\b0 \cf0 >> Auto layout is a constraint-based system, or a series of APIs, that determine how your application/views look on different sizes of devices. It offers a flexible, declarative system that allows user interfaces to adapt - across platforms, orientations, and device geometry. iOS developers use it so that their app can function and look good from a design standpoint across all devices and orientations that Apple has.
\b \
