What is a constraint? What are compression resistance and content hugging constraints?\
\pard\tx720\tx1440\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\tx5040\tx5760\tx6480\tx7200\tx7920\tx8640\pardirnatural\qr\partightenfactor0

\b0 \cf0 >> A constraint is a relationship between 2 views. It defines the relationship between views as the UI resizes for different devices and orientation. 
\b Compression resistance
\b0  constraints decide how strongly a view wants to preserve its intrinsic content. It keeps things from being clipped by pushing out. 
\b Content hugging
\b0  constraints resist extra space on things by applying pressure from the outside pulling in.
\b \
